-- Britain's Co-op confirms Myners to leave
-- 
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 10:38AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, April 10 (Reuters) - Britain's Co-operative Group <42TE.L> confirmed Paul Myners, a former government minister appointed four months ago to revive the scandal-hit group, had quit, making him the second top executive to walk away from the 170-year-old mutual in two months.

